# Naming Conventions

Consistent naming is critical for AI agents to predict file locations and understand code purpose.

## File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| **Store** | `{Name}Store.ts` | `PlayerStore.ts`, `CampaignStore.ts` |
| **Service** | `{Name}Service.ts` | `PhysicsService.ts`, `FirebaseService.ts` |
| **Component** | `{Name}.tsx` | `GameCanvas.tsx`, `TilePalette.tsx` |
| **Level** | `level_{name}.ts` | `level_test.ts`, `level_tutorial_01.ts` |
| **Types** | `{name}.types.ts` or `types.ts` | `level.types.ts` |
| **Helpers** | `helpers.ts` or `{name}.helpers.ts` | `helpers.ts` |
| **Constants** | `index.ts` in constants folder | `core/constants/index.ts` |

## Class & Function Naming

```typescript
// Classes: PascalCase
class PlayerStore { }
class PhysicsService { }

// Functions: camelCase
function createLevel() { }
function applyPlacements() { }

// Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
const TILE_SIZE = 64
const MAX_FALL_SPEED = 800

// Enums: PascalCase with SCREAMING members
enum CollisionType {
  EMPTY = 0,
  SOLID = 1,
}

// Interfaces: PascalCase, no "I" prefix
interface LevelDefinition { }  // ✅
interface ILevelDefinition { } // ❌
```

## Variable Naming

```typescript
// Observable state: camelCase nouns
x: number
vx: number  // velocity x (short form OK for physics)
isGrounded: boolean  // boolean prefix: is/has/can/should

// Methods: camelCase verbs
setPosition()
applyInput()
checkCollision()

// Private methods: camelCase (no underscore prefix)
private moveHorizontal() { }  // ✅
private _moveHorizontal() { } // ❌
```

## Level IDs

Level IDs use snake_case to match filename:

```typescript
// Filename: level_cave_escape.ts
export const level_cave_escape = createLevel(
  'level_cave_escape',  // ID matches filename
  'Cave Escape',        // Display name uses Title Case
  ...
)
```

## Grid Terminology

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `col` | Column (horizontal position, x-axis) |
| `row` | Row (vertical position, y-axis) |
| `x`, `y` | World pixel coordinates |
| `vx`, `vy` | Velocity components |
| `width`, `height` | Dimensions in tiles or pixels (context-dependent) |
